Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharpish turn. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Drawn by Petrie, Journal, 1884-5, p.181, 42. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0066.14. Name Aristanax.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0984)
